.TH man 1 "05 October 2015" "1.0" "location man page"
.SH NAME
location \- search information about a location in the world
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B location
[\fB\-e\fR]
[\fB\-s\fR \fIseparator\fR]
.I location
.SH DESCRIPTION
location queries the Yahoo! database for information about a location.
It displays the name of the location, the state, the country, the latitude,
the longitude and the WOEID.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-e
output in a format suitable for parsing, e.g. in shell scripts.
Otherwise a more human readable form will be used.
.TP
.BI "\-s " separator
Specifies the separator used to separate the fields when the
.B \-e
option is used. Otherwise this option is meaningless.
.SH EXAMPLES
location "Springfield"
.SH SEE ALSO
weather1)
.SH BUGS
No known bugs.
.SH AUTHOR
Wilfried Meindl <wilfried.meindl@gmail.com>

